==English==

===Etymology===
Greek (''hēdonē''), meaning ''pleasure.'' (Eng. usg. 1856)

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈhiːdənɪzəm/}}
*{{audio|en-us-hedonism.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

#{{philosophy}} The belief that [[pleasure]] or [[happiness]] is the highest good in life. Some [[hedonist]]s, such as the [[Epicurean]]s, have insisted that pleasure of the entire mind, not just pleasure of the senses, is the highest good.
#A general devotion to the pursuit of pleasure.

